solutions.content:
# Intuition
The problem is similar to jump game with atmost k jumps. Here instead of knowing the k before hand , we will get the k dynamically by nums[ind]

# Approach
First we will write the recursive logic and later memoise it.
From the 0th index we need to reach n-1 index in minimal possible steps.
- The base condition is that if we reach the end then return 0
- We will take a variable mini which will store the minimal jumps required to reach a particular index. We will initialise it with a large value.
- nums[ind] will define us how many steps atmost we can jump forward.
So we will have a loop from ind till ind+ k , (k=nums[ind]) and we will jump till there and update the mini.
(We need to take care that we do not jump out of the nums vector. ind+i <=n)
```
//Attaching recursive code
int dfs(int ind,int n,vector<int>&nums)
    {
        if(ind==n)return 0;
        int mini=1e9;
        int k=nums[ind];
        for(int i=1;i<=k;i++)
        {
            if(ind+i<=n)
            {
                int jump=1+dfs(ind+i,n,nums);
                mini=min(mini,jump);
            }
        }
        return mini;
    }

``` 
We will memoise it for optimisation.
**In main function we will pass dfs(0,n-1,nums)**
0 is the start index 
n-1 is the the last index of the nums (Mentioned in ques we need to jump till n-1th index)

# Complexity
- **Time complexity**:
TC would be O(n*k) where n is size of vector and k is the number of jumps we can take at each index.

- **Space complexity**:
We are doing recursion , so SC O(n) for recursion stack and a dp vector of O(n) space. Overall SC O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int dfs(int ind,int n,vector<int>&nums,vector<int>&dp)
    {
        if(ind==n)return 0;
        int mini=1e9;
        if(dp[ind]!=-1)return dp[ind];
        int k=nums[ind];
        for(int i=1;i<=k;i++)
        {
            if(ind+i<=n)
            {
                int jump=1+dfs(ind+i,n,nums,dp);
                mini=min(mini,jump);
            }
        }
        return dp[ind]=mini;
    }
    int jump(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        vector<int>dp(n,-1);
        return dfs(0,n-1,nums,dp);
    }
};
```

