Derived from [https://leetcode.com/problems/jump-game/discuss/541554/DP-and-Greedy](https://leetcode.com/problems/jump-game/discuss/541554/DP-and-Greedy).
### DP
Define **state(i)** as the minimum jumps to reach i
**state(i) = min(1 + state(j))** for each j that can jump to i.
The goal state is **state(nums.length - 1)**.
```
    public int jump(int[] nums) {
        int[] state = new int[nums.length];
        Arrays.fill(state, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        state[0] = 0;

        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
                if (nums[j] + j >= i) { // j can jump to i
                    state[i] = Math.min(state[i], state[j] + 1);
                }
            }
        }

        return state[nums.length - 1];
    }
```
### Greedy
Jump when we have to jump, and jump to the furthest position.
```
    public int jump(int[] nums) {
        if (nums.length < 2) {
            return 0;
        }
        int toJump = 0, numJumps = 0;

        // Build maxReach array
        int[] maxReach = new int[nums.length];
        maxReach[0] = nums[0];
        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
            // Assuming we can jump to nums[i], we can reach up to maxReach[i]
