# Approach
1. We can use a greedy approach to solve this problem. We can keep track of the current farthest index we can reach and the current end of the current jump.
2. We can keep track of the current farthest index we can reach by taking the maximum of the current farthest index and the current index + the value at the current index.
3. If the current index is equal to the current end of the current jump, we can increment the number of jumps and set the current end of the current jump to the current farthest index.
4. We can return the number of jumps.

